article.headline: Illinois St. 70, Ball St. 57
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Levi Dyer scored 29 points on 11-of-13 shooting to lead Illinois State to a 70-57 win over Ball State on Saturday. Dyer scored the first eight points for the Redbirds, helping to lift Illinois State to a 31-23 halftime lead. After trailing throughout the second half, Ahmaad Cook hit a 3-pointer for Ball State that pulled the Cardinals to within one at 50-49 with 7:05 left. But the Redbirds answered with a 9-0 run to put the game out of reach. Anthony Slack scored 10 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Redbirds. Osiris Eldridge and Greg Dilligard scored 10 points apiece for Illinois State. Peyton Stovall scored 18 points to lead Ball State (9-17), and Cook added 16.
